x-height (Mobile).$description: Check the x-height of your font at 1rem and set it as close as possible. This is by default base mobile heading size (defaults to 18px)

x-height (Desktop).$description: Check the x-height of your font at 1rem and set it as close as possible. This is by default base desktop heading size (defaults to: 20px)

x-height (Mobile).$description: Check the x-height of your font at 1rem and set it as close as possible. This is by default base mobile body font size (defaults to 16px)

x-height (Desktop).$description: Check the x-height of your font at 1rem and set it as close as possible. This is by default base desktop body font size (defaults to 18px)

All.$description:
Set this value to a fixed color or reference any other color from the color tab. (for example: {Neutral.Black}).

You can also specify different colors for any heading level independently using the following tokens.

By default this token applies to all heading levels.

Main.$description: The brand’s primary color (The main identifying brand color – also often the action color).
The brand’s second most used color.
The brand’s third most used color.
The brand’s base color (typically best if a dark version of the base is chosen) – most commonly used for backgrounds and text.
Black and white, plus shades of grey.
The brand’s Semantic.Success color (The main identifying brand color – also often the action color).
The brand’s Semantic.Warning color (The main identifying brand color – also often the action color).
The brand’s Semantic.Info color (The main identifying brand color – also often the action color).
The brand’s Semantic.Danger color (The main identifying brand color – also often the action color).
